The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Thursday , June 5 , 2008                    
	Whats on    Emergency services like hospitals, blood banks, medicine shops, and hearses will be outside the purview of the bandh.    State and central government departments will be open but employees may not turn up.    Taxi associations said there is no bar on taxis plying but most will stay off the road, fearing damage by bandh supporters.    Metro Railway authorities said they will operate trains according to schedule but the services may be withdrawn depending on the bandh situation.    Long-distance and suburban trains of Eastern and South Eastern Railway will ply according to schedule, provided there is no obstruction on the tracks.    All 19 markets run by the Calcutta Municipal Corporation will be officially open but shopkeepers are likely to stay away.    
	Whats off    State buses and trams will not ply.    Private buses and autorickshaws will not ply.    The morning flights of Jet Airways may be preponed, while the day and afternoon flights may be rescheduled, combined or cancelled (emergency contact number: 39893333).    Kingfisher Airlines morning flights to Delhi, Mumbai, Bhubaneswar and Agartala have been cancelled. Flight IT 2554 (Calcutta-Raipur) will leave at 7pm instead of 3.30pm, flight IT 2503 (Calcutta-Bhubaneswar) will leave at 7.30pm instead of 6.40pm, flight IT 432 (Calcutta-Hyderabad) will leave at 7.30pm instead of 5.55pm (emergency toll-free number: 18002093030/    8001800101).    Air India will try to operate all flights on time, depending on the bandh situation. They may reschedule and combine some afternoon and evening flights (emergency toll-free number: 18001801407)    Officials of IndiGo and Deccan airlines were not available for information.    Most malls and art galleries will be closed during the day.                                                                                                                                                                 
